50|$|The European Securities and Markets Authority (ESMA) began {{developing}} {{technical standards}} on regulation of OTC derivatives, <b>central</b> <b>counterparties</b> and trade repositories to implement EMIR in February 2012. ESMA released a discussion {{paper on the}} topic, and in March 2012, the Authority held a public discussion in Paris to receive input on the questions put forth in the discussion paper.|$|E
